Former Senator Wendell Ford has passed away, and President Obama and the First Lady expressed their sadness at the news. Wendell Ford was a veteran, businessman, Governor, and four-term Senator from Kentucky. He dedicated his life to serving the people of Kentucky and believed in fairness, equal access to the polls, fair wages for workers, and providing support to those seeking employment. He also mentored many young people who entered public service. Wendell Ford was highly admired in politics and had a significant impact on Kentucky. The President and the First Lady send their condolences to his wife Jean and the rest of the Ford family.